The defendant Jennette M Kilgore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Case called at 10:06 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Jennette M Kilgore in court with Attorney Michael C. Witt. ADA Theresa A Beck appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On Motion of the State, the Court ADDS COUNT #3, Possession of Drug Paraphernalia 961.573(1), a Misdemeanor
Court charges ADA Beck to file AMENDED information by end of business 8/27/14

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Counts #1, #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered. on Counts #2 & #3 and stays Judgment on Count #1.
Court adopts Deferred Proscution Agreement on Count #1

On Counts #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, concurrent, each count & concurrent to DPA in Count #1, with conditions:
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--Random urinalyses
 or other drug testing (twice per month for the 1st 6 months, then at least once 1x/mth for remainder of probation)
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program ro some combinatin of those, per Agent
--No possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--Take all prescribed medications only as presribed
--50 hours of community service designed to educate youth and the public about the dangers of opiates, per Agent (these hours are the same hours that are required as part of DPA in Count #1)
--To pay costs of $486 ($243 each count)
--To pay $400 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)
--No contact with any know drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate, per Agent and incidental contact for purposes for education/employment, per Agent.  The Court grants an exception that the defendant may have contact with Kevin Stevens, but does allow Agent to withdraw the Court's approval of contact, if Agent deems it appropriate. 

Days credit for time already served: 0 days

The Court indicates that if the DNA surcharge is found to be unconstitutional, and the Defendant has not yet paid the surcharge, then the Judgment of Conviction is to be amended to remove the surcharge payment requirement.  If the DNA surcharge has been paid and the ruling that found the DNA surcharge unconstitutional directs the clerks to reimburse the amount paid, then the clerk is to refund the amount paid to the Defendant. If the reimbursement is not mandated, then the amount will be kept.

case called at 2:13pm. 
Defendant Jennette M Kilgore in court with Attorney Michael C. Witt.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights given; plea of " No Contest " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Kilgore guilty of Count #1, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count # 2.

On Count # 1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Kilgore on Probation for two years, with conditions:

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment if/as required by the Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--random urinalyses or other drug testing, to occur at least twice per month for the first six months, and thereafter at least once per month for the remainder of the Probation term
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take all prescribed medications only as prescribed
--to perform 100 hours of community service, with at least 50 of those hours are to be designed to educate youth and the public about the dangers of opiates, as approved by the Agent
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate by the Agent, and except for the community service work as deemed appropriate by the Agent, and except for incidental contact for employment or educational programming as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain fulltime employment and/or educational program as required by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision
--to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge plus $25 in drug testing fees


Days credit for time already served:  0  days
As the Court addresses the request of the Defense for expungement, the Court raises that expungement is not available for Ms. Kilgore due to her age.  
On request of Attorney Witt, the Court allows the Defendant to withdraw her plea; the Judgment of Conviction is vacated.  
recess 2:32pm.
